  <bioghist id="aspace_eb4de15e6bf6e6d42bd383e624da5e89">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Traveler, translator, writer, man of letters, non-resident professor of German literature at Cornell University.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_d00cad95e566a7caa120bc0755c6cb27">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, journals, notebooks, scrapbooks, manuscripts, diaries, clippings, articles, sketches, and autobiographical notes pertaining to Taylor's life as a writer and traveler in North Africa, Scandinavia, Europe, and the Middle East.</p><p> Also, a watercolor landscape by Taylor acquired by Dr. Francis Harvey Green and given to William F. Rochow in 1950, with "Gems of Thought," a card with excerpts from Taylor's writings selected by Green.</p>  </scopecontent>
